"Do NOT go to Nandi Hills without watching this!"
We went to Nandi Hills on a Friday... but guess what?
They weren't allowing 4-wheelers!
That meant... we had to walk 9 KM uphill to reach the viewpoint.
We started our climb at 6 AM...
And reached the top by 9.
It was one of the toughest walks ever
We even took a few shortcuts through the forest to save time... And every step felt like a mini adventure!

But when we finally reached it felt like a personal victory! The views were totally worth It
We clicked tons of pictures, sipped on hot chai
had some food
And just soaked in the breathtaking scenery.
Then... it was time to climb down another 9 KM!
Finally made it back to the checkpoint - tired but so fulfilled!
